<div id="instructions" style="visibility:hidden"></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">How to Make Instant Pot  Lo Mein with Beef and Broccoli  (Step by Step Instructions) </h2>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>Turn on <strong><em>Saute</em></strong> mode.</li>



<li>Saute beef and remove.</li>



<li>Saute vegetables and remove. </li>



<li>Saute ginger and garlic.</li>



<li>Stir in broth, beef, mushrooms, and spices.</li>



<li>Add noodles in layers.</li>



<li>Pressure cook for 8 minutes.</li>



<li>Do a quick release in bursts.</li>



<li>Add back reserved broccoli.</li>



<li>Stir in sesame seeds.</li>
</ol>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How to Turn on <strong><em>Saute</em></strong> Mode</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="3000" height="1500" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%203000%201500'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Instant Pot Ultra Duo Saute Function collage - arrows pointing to Saute in Duo and Ultra - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-4666" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Duo-Saute-Function-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg 3000w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Duo-Saute-Function-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x150.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Duo-Saute-Function-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x384.jpg 768w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Duo-Saute-Function-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x512.jpg 1024w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 3000px) 100vw, 3000px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Duo-Saute-Function-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Duo-Saute-Function-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="3000" height="1500" src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Duo-Saute-Function-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg" alt="Instant Pot Ultra Duo Saute Function collage - arrows pointing to Saute in Duo and Ultra - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-4666" srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Duo-Saute-Function-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg 3000w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Duo-Saute-Function-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x150.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Duo-Saute-Function-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x384.jpg 768w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Duo-Saute-Function-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x512.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 3000px) 100vw, 3000px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Duo-Saute-Function-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ul class="wp-block-list"><li><strong>Instant Pot DUO:</strong>&nbsp; Select the <em><strong>Saute</strong></em> function.</li><li><strong>Instant Pot ULTRA:</strong>&nbsp; Select the <em><strong>Saute</strong></em> function and press <em><strong>Start</strong></em>. </li></ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Saute Beef and Remove from Heat</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="341" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201024%20341'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Instant Pot Lo Mein with Beef and Broccoli Instructions collage - oil in inner pot, beef, remove beef - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9846" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-1-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-1-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-1-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-1-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-1-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="341" src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-1-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg" alt="Instant Pot Lo Mein with Beef and Broccoli Instructions collage - oil in inner pot, beef, remove beef - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9846" srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-1-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-1-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-1-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-1-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Once the inner pot has heated up, add 1 tablespoon of oil.</li>



<li>Saute the beef until browned.</li>



<li>Use a slotted spoon to transfer beef to a bowl and set aside.</li>
</ul>



<p><strong><em>TIP: To prevent overcrowding, saute the beef in batches if necessary.</em></strong></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Saute Vegetables and Remove from Heat</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="341" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201024%20341'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Instant Pot Lo Mein with Beef and Broccoli Instructions collage - broccoli, soy sauce, remove broccoli - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9847" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-2-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-2-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-2-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-2-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-2-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="341" src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-2-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg" alt="Instant Pot Lo Mein with Beef and Broccoli Instructions collage - broccoli, soy sauce, remove broccoli - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9847" srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-2-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-2-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-2-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-2-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Add a teaspoon of oil to the inner pot.</li>



<li>Saute the broccoli, stirring frequently.  The liquid from the vegetables should deglaze the inner pot; scrape the brown bits so nothing is stuck to the bottom.</li>



<li>Add ½ teaspoon soy sauce to the broccoli and stir until crisp-tender.</li>



<li>Use a slotted spoon to transfer the broccoli to a bowl and set aside.</li>



<li>Select &lsquo;Cancel&rsquo;.  The ginger and garlic will cook in the residual heat.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Saute Ginger and Garlic</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="341" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201024%20341'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Instant Pot Lo Mein with Beef and Broccoli Instructions collage - oil, ginger, and garlic, stirring - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9848" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-3-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-3-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-3-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-3-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-3-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="341" src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-3-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg" alt="Instant Pot Lo Mein with Beef and Broccoli Instructions collage - oil, ginger, and garlic, stirring - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9848" srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-3-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-3-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-3-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-3-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Add the remaining oil to the inner pot.</li>



<li>Add the ginger and garlic to the inner pot.</li>



<li>Stir constantly for 30 seconds to a minute, until fragrant.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Stir in Broth, Beef, Mushrooms, and Spices.</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="341" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201024%20341'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Instant Pot Lo Mein with Beef and Broccoli Instructions collage - broth, mushrooms, spices -- Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9849" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-4-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-4-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-4-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-4-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-4-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="341" src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-4-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg" alt="Instant Pot Lo Mein with Beef and Broccoli Instructions collage - broth, mushrooms, spices -- Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9849" srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-4-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-4-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-4-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-4-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Add a few tablespoons of broth to deglaze the inner pot, scraping up any brown bits until they come loose.</li>



<li>Stir in broth, rice wine, sesame oil, remaining soy sauce, oyster sauce,  white pepper, crushed red pepper flakes, brown sugar, mushrooms, and reserved beef.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Add Noodles in Layers</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="341" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201024%20341'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Instant Pot Lo Mein with Beef and Broccoli Instructions collage - spaghetti in one layer, more layers in crisscross pattern, push down with spatula - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9850" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-5-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-5-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-5-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-5-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-5-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="341" src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-5-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg" alt="Instant Pot Lo Mein with Beef and Broccoli Instructions collage - spaghetti in one layer, more layers in crisscross pattern, push down with spatula - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9850" srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-5-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-5-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-5-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-5-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Add the noodles in batches, alternating in a criss-cross pattern. (See video for more details).</li>



<li>Gently push down on the noodles with a spatula, pressing down until all the noodles are wet. This might take about 20 to 30 seconds. </li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Instant Pot Duo Pressure Cook 8 minutes</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="2560" height="700" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202560%20700'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Instant Pot Duo Manual mode 8 minutes collage - close lid, press manual, press + -, display says 8 - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-8005" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Instant-Pot-Manual-mode-8-minutes.jpg 2560w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Instant-Pot-Manual-mode-8-minutes-300x82.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Instant-Pot-Manual-mode-8-minutes-768x210.jpg 768w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Instant-Pot-Manual-mode-8-minutes-1024x280.jpg 1024w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Instant-Pot-Manual-mode-8-minutes.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Instant-Pot-Manual-mode-8-minutes.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="2560" height="700" src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Instant-Pot-Manual-mode-8-minutes.jpg" alt="Instant Pot Duo Manual mode 8 minutes collage - close lid, press manual, press + -, display says 8 - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-8005" srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Instant-Pot-Manual-mode-8-minutes.jpg 2560w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Instant-Pot-Manual-mode-8-minutes-300x82.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Instant-Pot-Manual-mode-8-minutes-768x210.jpg 768w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Instant-Pot-Manual-mode-8-minutes-1024x280.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Instant-Pot-Manual-mode-8-minutes.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Close the lid and make sure the steam release handle is in the <strong><em>Sealing</em></strong> position.</li><li>Press &lsquo;Manual&rsquo; (or <strong><em>Pressure Cook</em></strong>) and <strong><em>+</em></strong> or <strong><em>&ndash;</em></strong> until the display reads <strong><em>8</em></strong> (8 minutes). </li></ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Instant Pot Ultra Pressure Cook 8 minutes</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="3000" height="1000" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%203000%201000'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Instant Pot Ultra pressure cook 8 minutes collage - close Instant Pot Ultra, set time to 00:08 and select Pressure Cook, press start - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9856" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Pressure-Cook-for-8-minutes-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg 3000w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Pressure-Cook-for-8-minutes-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Pressure-Cook-for-8-minutes-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Pressure-Cook-for-8-minutes-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 3000px) 100vw, 3000px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Pressure-Cook-for-8-minutes-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Pressure-Cook-for-8-minutes-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="3000" height="1000" src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Pressure-Cook-for-8-minutes-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg" alt="Instant Pot Ultra pressure cook 8 minutes collage - close Instant Pot Ultra, set time to 00:08 and select Pressure Cook, press start - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9856" srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Pressure-Cook-for-8-minutes-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg 3000w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Pressure-Cook-for-8-minutes-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Pressure-Cook-for-8-minutes-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Pressure-Cook-for-8-minutes-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 3000px) 100vw, 3000px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Pressure-Cook-for-8-minutes-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ul class="wp-block-list"><li> Close the lid.</li><li> Select <strong><em>Pressure Cook</em></strong> mode and adjust the time to 8 minutes (<strong><em>00:08</em></strong>).</li><li> Press <strong><em>Start</em></strong>. </li></ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Pressure Cooking Process (Duo and Ultra)</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="3000" height="1000" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%203000%201000'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Instant Pot Duo Pressure Cooking collage - display shows On, float valve is down, display shows L0:00 - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-4712" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Duo-Pressure-Cooking.jpg 3000w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Duo-Pressure-Cooking-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Duo-Pressure-Cooking-768x256.jpg 768w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Duo-Pressure-Cooking-1024x341.jpg 1024w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 3000px) 100vw, 3000px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Duo-Pressure-Cooking.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Duo-Pressure-Cooking.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="3000" height="1000" src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Duo-Pressure-Cooking.jpg" alt="Instant Pot Duo Pressure Cooking collage - display shows On, float valve is down, display shows L0:00 - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-4712" srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Duo-Pressure-Cooking.jpg 3000w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Duo-Pressure-Cooking-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Duo-Pressure-Cooking-768x256.jpg 768w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Duo-Pressure-Cooking-1024x341.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 3000px) 100vw, 3000px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Duo-Pressure-Cooking.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="3000" height="1000" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%203000%201000'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Instant Pot Ultra pressure cooking collage - Ultra display shows On, float valve is up, display shows 00 00 - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-4713" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-pressure-cooking.jpg 3000w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-pressure-cooking-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-pressure-cooking-768x256.jpg 768w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-pressure-cooking-1024x341.jpg 1024w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 3000px) 100vw, 3000px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-pressure-cooking.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-pressure-cooking.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="3000" height="1000" src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-pressure-cooking.jpg" alt="Instant Pot Ultra pressure cooking collage - Ultra display shows On, float valve is up, display shows 00 00 - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-4713" srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-pressure-cooking.jpg 3000w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-pressure-cooking-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-pressure-cooking-768x256.jpg 768w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-pressure-cooking-1024x341.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 3000px) 100vw, 3000px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-pressure-cooking.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Instant Pot display will change to <strong><em>On</em></strong>.</li><li>Once the Instant Pot is pressurized, the float valve will go up.</li><li>The display will count down to 0; it will then switch to <strong><em>Keep Warm</em></strong> mode and display <strong><em>L0:00</em></strong>&nbsp; or <strong><em>00 00</em></strong> and begin to count up the number of minutes since pressure cooking completed.</li></ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How to Quick Release Pressure (QR) on the DUO</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="3000" height="1000" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%203000%201000'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Instant Pot Quick Release collage - move handle to venting, float valve down, lid propped open - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9594" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Instant-Pot-Duo-Quick-Release-QR-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg 3000w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Instant-Pot-Duo-Quick-Release-QR-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Instant-Pot-Duo-Quick-Release-QR-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Instant-Pot-Duo-Quick-Release-QR-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 3000px) 100vw, 3000px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Instant-Pot-Duo-Quick-Release-QR-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Instant-Pot-Duo-Quick-Release-QR-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="3000" height="1000" src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Instant-Pot-Duo-Quick-Release-QR-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg" alt="Instant Pot Quick Release collage - move handle to venting, float valve down, lid propped open - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9594" srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Instant-Pot-Duo-Quick-Release-QR-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg 3000w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Instant-Pot-Duo-Quick-Release-QR-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Instant-Pot-Duo-Quick-Release-QR-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Instant-Pot-Duo-Quick-Release-QR-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 3000px) 100vw, 3000px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Instant-Pot-Duo-Quick-Release-QR-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ul class="wp-block-list"><li> Move the steam release handle to <em><strong>Venting</strong></em>.  Steam will come out of the steam release handle.</li><li>When your Instant Pot is depressurized, the float valve will be in the down position.</li><li>Press <em><strong>Cancel</strong> </em>and open the Instant Pot. </li></ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How to Quick Release Pressure (QR) on the ULTRA</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="3000" height="1000" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%203000%201000'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Instant Pot Ultra Release Steam and Open collage - press steam release button, float valve in down position, Instant Pot Ultra is open - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-4764" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Release-Steam-and-Open-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg 3000w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Release-Steam-and-Open-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Release-Steam-and-Open-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Release-Steam-and-Open-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 3000px) 100vw, 3000px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Release-Steam-and-Open-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Release-Steam-and-Open-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="3000" height="1000" src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Release-Steam-and-Open-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg" alt="Instant Pot Ultra Release Steam and Open collage - press steam release button, float valve in down position, Instant Pot Ultra is open - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-4764" srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Release-Steam-and-Open-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg 3000w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Release-Steam-and-Open-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Release-Steam-and-Open-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Release-Steam-and-Open-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 3000px) 100vw, 3000px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Instant-Pot-Ultra-Release-Steam-and-Open-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Press down on the Steam Release Button until it locks into place, and steam begins to come out of the Steam Release Valve.</li><li>When your Instant Pot is depressurized, the float valve will be in the down position.</li><li>Press <em><strong>Cancel</strong></em> and open the Instant Pot.</li></ul>



<p><em><strong>[Find out more about the <a href="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/instant-pot-natural-release-or-quick-release/">pressure release methods and how and when to use them</a>. ]</strong></em></p>



<div class="wp-block-group light-box-style"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow">
<p class="has-medium-font-size">&#9999;&#65039; <strong>Pro Tip for Releasing Pressure in Small Bursts</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>For some foods such as noodles, I find it helpful to release the steam in small bursts: less than 1-second intervals. &nbsp;Once the steam coming out is less forceful, release the remaining pressure in a steady stream. Read more about the <a href="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/instant-pot-natural-release-or-quick-release/">different pressure release methods</a>.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Add Reserved Broccoli</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="341" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201024%20341'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Instant Pot Lo Mein with Beef and Broccoli Instructions collage - cooked spaghetti, stirred, close lid - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9851" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-6-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-6-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-6-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-6-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-6-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="341" src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-6-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg" alt="Instant Pot Lo Mein with Beef and Broccoli Instructions collage - cooked spaghetti, stirred, close lid - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9851" srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-6-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-6-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-6-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-6-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Stir the noodles, beef, and mushrooms, breaking up any clumps of noodles with a fork.</li>



<li>Add in the reserved broccoli.</li>



<li>If there is liquid left in the Instant Pot Lo Mein, let the noodles rest for 5 to 10 minutes.   They should thicken up.  I close the lid but you can also leave it open. *</li>
</ul>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>You can also select <strong><em>Saute</em></strong> and allow the liquid to evaporate. </li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Stir in Sesame Seeds</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="341" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201024%20341'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Instant Pot Lo Mein with Beef and Broccoli Instructions opened lid, sesame seeds, stirred - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9852" data-lazy-srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-7-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-7-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-7-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-7-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg" data-lazy-src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-7-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="341" src="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-7-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg" alt="Instant Pot Lo Mein with Beef and Broccoli Instructions opened lid, sesame seeds, stirred - Paint the Kitchen Red" class="wp-image-9852" srcset="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-7-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-1024x341.jpg 1024w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-7-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-7-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red-768x256.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" data-pin-media="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Instant-Pot-Lo-Mein-with-Beef-and-Broccoli-Instructions-7-Paint-the-Kitchen-Red.jpg"></noscript></figure>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Open the lid.</li>



<li>Add sesame seeds to the Instant Pot Lo Mein Noodles.</li>



<li>Stir all ingredients.</li>
</ul>



