yle-type: disc;" data-uid="2"><span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">lb.</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Chuck-Roast-Boneless-Pasture-Raised/dp/B07815GM3N?almBrandId=VUZHIFdob2xlIEZvb2Rz&amp;crid=1GSJJ9JY65U24&amp;fpw=alm&amp;keywords=beef+chuck&amp;qid=1671139825&amp;s=wholefoods&amp;sprefix=beef+chuck+%2Cwholefoods%2C111&amp;sr=1-2&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=paintthekitch-20&amp;linkId=9d3d1fab607b06692c8b48481382b631&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl" data-eafl-id="12217" data-eafl-parsed="1" class="eafl-link eafl-link-text eafl-link-direct" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">beef chuck</a></span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">(500 grams) or beef round roast, sliced very thin</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;" data-uid="4"><span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/365-Everyday-Value-Organic-Broccoli/dp/B077LF2ZMR?crid=5DBAOQFFUKAL&amp;keywords=broccoli&amp;qid=1679606553&amp;sprefix=broccoli%2Caps%2C134&amp;sr=8-8&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=paintthekitch-20&amp;linkId=f2439c156779577dfae074a506a9b018&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl" data-eafl-id="26754" data-eafl-parsed="1" class="eafl-link eafl-link-text eafl-link-direct" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">broccoli florets</a></span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;" data-uid="6"><span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">¼</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Kikkoman-Japan-Made-Sauce-Ounce/dp/B003XDIU30/ref=as_li_ss_tl?keywords=soy+sauce&amp;qid=1575489098&amp;s=grocery&amp;sr=1-5&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=paintthekitch-20&amp;linkId=9e2b2a1eb45ed26e5446e8c78c0ee95f&amp;language=en_US" data-eafl-id="10636" data-eafl-parsed="1" class="eafl-link eafl-link-text eafl-link-direct" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">soy sauce</a></span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;" data-uid="8"><span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Ginger-People-Organic-Minced-6-7/dp/B00IV6ZM58/ref=as_li_ss_tl?SubscriptionId=AKIAJQ7BMFWFJPB3SDRQ&amp;th=1&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=paintthekitch-20&amp;linkId=5a3dc6c354fd16d3a1a7aec451d51ee5&amp;language=en_US" data-eafl-id="15441" data-eafl-parsed="1" class="eafl-link eafl-link-text eafl-link-direct" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">ginger</a></span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">minced</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;" data-uid="10"><span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Garlic-Organic-1-Each/dp/B0788FLWK1?dchild=1&amp;keywords=garlic&amp;qid=1627755328&amp;sr=8-2&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=paintthekitch-20&amp;linkId=85abf2c73844ad1eae5e330dfe742c19&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl" data-eafl-id="10855" data-eafl-parsed="1" class="eafl-link eafl-link-text eafl-link-direct" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">garlic</a></span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">minced</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;" data-uid="12"><span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Swanson-Less-Sodium-Beef-Broth/dp/B01LWIN49A/ref=as_li_ss_tl?dchild=1&amp;fpw=pantry&amp;keywords=beef+broth&amp;qid=1591393506&amp;s=pantry&amp;sr=8-4&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=paintthekitch-20&amp;linkId=99fbfbffd9379603acb5073ed4319a0c&amp;language=en_US" data-eafl-id="12809" data-eafl-parsed="1" class="eafl-link eafl-link-text eafl-link-direct" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">beef broth</a></span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">plus more to deglaze</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;" data-uid="14"><span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B071S8ZDG2/ref=as_li_ss_tl?&amp;th=1&amp;psc=1&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=paintthekitch-20&amp;linkId=3fc97c49560645b4f2682d993c213ad1&amp;language=en_US" class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-link" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Chinese rice wine</a></span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">Shaoxing</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;" data-uid="16"><span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Kadoya-100-Pure-Sesame-Oil/dp/B008K0Y3FK?dchild=1&amp;keywords=sesame+oil&amp;qid=1613522102&amp;sr=8-3&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=paintthekitch-20&amp;linkId=82c9dd0614fa1237b1df4979fceb6324&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl" data-eafl-id="15739" data-eafl-parsed="1" class="eafl-link eafl-link-text eafl-link-direct" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">sesame oil</a></span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;" data-uid="18"><span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Lee-Kum-Kee-Oyster-Premium/dp/B00KO3F1X4?ac_md=1-0-TGVlIEt1bSBLZWU%3D-ac_d_br_brs_brs&amp;content-id=amzn1.sym.6e5839ef-173a-469e-9144-6369d9efedac%3Aamzn1.sym.6e5839ef-173a-469e-9144-6369d9efedac&amp;crid=1I2QLDTR4ACEJ&amp;cv_ct_cx=oyster+sauce&amp;keywords=oyster+sauce&amp;pd_rd_i=B00KO3F1X4&amp;pd_rd_r=2aef67ef-719c-4641-b368-d4ef979b8544&amp;pd_rd_w=CV61h&amp;pd_rd_wg=YjRm3&amp;pf_rd_p=6e5839ef-173a-469e-9144-6369d9efedac&amp;pf_rd_r=8YB0VRJ9MFYRBY9JWHR0&amp;qid=1671548670&amp;sprefix=oyster+sauc%2Caps%2C143&amp;sr=1-1-66a9a48c-983d-48d6-91a8-55e5ebc7ab50&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=paintthekitch-20&amp;linkId=7c575726b7a18cc1ab39949cb6d9bc21&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl" data-eafl-id="10632" data-eafl-parsed="1" class="eafl-link eafl-link-text eafl-link-direct" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">oyster sauce</a></span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;" data-uid="20"><span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">¼</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Simply-Organic-Pepper-White-Ounce/dp/B00AJRKPE0/ref=as_li_ss_tl?crid=1MILEJHIXJIX2&amp;keywords=white+pepper&amp;qid=1576336664&amp;s=grocery&amp;sprefix=white+pepper,grocery,551&amp;sr=1-6&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=paintthekitch-20&amp;linkId=66cc31e537b80160b1ced6c0f581045b&amp;language=en_US" data-eafl-id="10849" data-eafl-parsed="1" class="eafl-link eafl-link-text eafl-link-direct" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">white pepper</a></span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;" data-uid="22"><span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">½</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B000WS3AJ8/ref=as_li_ss_tl?&amp;th=1&amp;psc=1&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=paintthekitch-20&amp;linkId=836b9fe4e48cda5797268e55db548e6d&amp;language=en_US" data-eafl-id="11363" data-eafl-parsed="1" class="eafl-link eafl-link-text eafl-link-direct" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">crushed red pepper</a></span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">or to taste</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;" data-uid="24"><span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B007FA1EBW/ref=as_li_ss_tl?&amp;th=1&amp;psc=1&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=paintthekitch-20&amp;linkId=bc003b1ffb9f916a1e20f844c2dee3d9&amp;language=en_US" data-eafl-id="10716" data-eafl-parsed="1" class="eafl-link eafl-link-text eafl-link-direct" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">brown sugar</a></span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;" data-uid="26"><span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/365-Everyday-Value-Organic-Mushrooms/dp/B07NQCGBD7?dchild=1&amp;keywords=mushrooms&amp;qid=1627427704&amp;sr=8-2&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=paintthekitch-20&amp;linkId=9b42efc8cc4a13d4f6fb8a0ae0128cb7&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl" data-eafl-id="18123" data-eafl-parsed="1" class="eafl-link eafl-link-text eafl-link-direct" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">mushrooms</a></span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">sliced</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;" data-uid="28"><span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">8</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00IB1DKN4/ref=as_li_ss_tl?&amp;th=1&amp;psc=1&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=paintthekitch-20&amp;linkId=de4b51e525cb8a95e4ad3a4293436795&amp;language=en_US" data-eafl-id="11927" data-eafl-parsed="1" class="eafl-link eafl-link-text eafl-link-direct" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">dry spaghetti</a></span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">(Barilla No. 5) &ndash; 226 grams &ndash; strands broken in half</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;" data-uid="30"><span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 ½</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Simply-Organic-Bottle-Sesame-Whole/dp/B000WR2OGY?dchild=1&amp;keywords=sesame+seeds&amp;qid=1627756070&amp;sr=8-10&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=paintthekitch-20&amp;linkId=b9866ca451ab3fae648f599f9a00acdd&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl" data-eafl-id="18092" data-eafl-parsed="1" class="eafl-link eafl-link-text eafl-link-direct" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">sesame seeds</a></span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">toasted</span></li></ul></div></div>
<div id="recipe-video"></div><div id="wprm-recipe-video-container-9863" class="wprm-recipe-video-container"><div class="wprm-recipe-video"><div id="lj40hzn9lgbi6xm19rfb" data-volume="70" data-ratio="16:9"></div>
<script type="text/javascript" src="//video.mediavine.com/videos/lj40hzn9lgbi6xm19rfb.js" async data-noptimize></script></div></div>

<div id="recipe-9863-instructions" class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-recipe-9863-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal" data-recipe="9863"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header wprm-block-text-uppercase wprm-align-left wprm-header-decoration-line wprm-header-has-actions" style="">Instructions<div class="wprm-decoration-line" style="border-color: #e0e0e0;"></div>&nbsp;</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-9863-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">In <em><strong>Saute</strong></em> mode, heat Instant Pot.  Once Instant Pot is hot, add 1 tablespoon vegetable oil.  Saute <span class="wprm-inline-ingredient wprm-inline-ingredient-9863-2 wprm-block-text-bold">1 lb. beef chuck</span> until beef is browned on all sides.  To prevent overcrowding, saute beef in batches if needed.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-9863-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Transfer beef to a medium bowl and set aside.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-9863-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Add 1 teaspoon of oil to the inner pot and saute the <span class="wprm-inline-ingredient wprm-inline-ingredient-9863-4 wprm-block-text-bold">5 cups broccoli florets</span> until crisp-tender.  Add ½ teaspoon soy sauce to the broccoli, saute briefly and remove to a medium bowl.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-9863-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Select <em><strong>Cancel</strong></em> and turn off the Instant Pot.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-9863-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Add remaining oil to the Instant Pot.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-9863-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Add <span class="wprm-inline-ingredient wprm-inline-ingredient-9863-8 wprm-block-text-bold">2 tablespoon ginger</span> and <span class="wprm-inline-ingredient wprm-inline-ingredient-9863-10 wprm-block-text-bold">2 tablespoon garlic</span>; stir for 30 seconds.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-9863-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Deglaze the inner pot by adding a tablespoon or two of broth to the hot inner pot, and scraping until the brown bits come loose.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-9863-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Stir in <span class="wprm-inline-ingredient wprm-inline-ingredient-9863-12 wprm-block-text-bold">2 cups beef broth</span>, <span class="wprm-inline-ingredient wprm-inline-ingredient-9863-14 wprm-block-text-bold">2 tablespoon Chinese rice wine</span>, <span class="wprm-inline-ingredient wprm-inline-ingredient-9863-16 wprm-block-text-bold">2 teaspoon sesame oil</span>, remaining soy sauce, <span class="wprm-inline-ingredient wprm-inline-ingredient-9863-18 wprm-block-text-bold">2 teaspoon oyster sauce</span>, <span class="wprm-inline-ingredient wprm-inline-ingredient-9863-20 wprm-block-text-bold">¼ teaspoon white pepper</span>, <span class="wprm-inline-ingredient wprm-inline-ingredient-9863-22 wprm-block-text-bold">½ teaspoon crushed red pepper</span>, <span class="wprm-inline-ingredient wprm-inline-ingredient-9863-24 wprm-block-text-bold">2 tablespoon brown sugar</span>, <span class="wprm-inline-ingredient wprm-inline-ingredient-9863-26 wprm-block-text-bold">2 cups mushrooms</span> and reserved beef.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-9863-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Divide <span class="wprm-inline-ingredient wprm-inline-ingredient-9863-28 wprm-block-text-bold">8 oz dry spaghetti</span> into four batches. Add noodles to the inner pot in batches: add one-fourth of noodles into the broth, fanning it out. Repeat with remaining batches, in a criss-cross pattern (see blog post for step by step photos or watch the video).</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-9863-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Using a spatula, gently push down on the spaghetti until it's submerged in the broth. This might take 20 to 30 seconds.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-9863-step-0-10" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Close the lid and pressure cook the noodles for 8 minutes on <em><strong>High Pressure</strong></em>.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-9863-step-0-11" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;"> Do a quick release, in small bursts. See <a href="#tips">Tips</a>.   <strong>[</strong><em><strong>Read More: </strong></em><a href="https://www.paintthekitchenred.com/instant-pot-natural-release-or-quick-release/"><em><strong>The Different Pressure Release Methods</strong></em></a><em><strong>]</strong></em></span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-9863-step-0-12" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Open the lid and stir in the broccoli.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-9863-step-0-13" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">If there's too much liquid remaining in the inner pot, allow the noodles to rest for 5 to 10 minutes.  The Instant Pot Lo Mein Noodles should thicken up. *</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-9863-step-0-14" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px;"><span style="display: block;">Select <em><strong>Cancel</strong></em> and stir in <span class="wprm-inline-ingredient wprm-inline-ingredient-9863-30 wprm-block-text-bold">1 ½ teaspoon sesame seeds</span>.</span></div></li></ul></div></div>

<div id="recipe-9863-notes" class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header wprm-block-text-uppercase wprm-align-left wprm-header-decoration-line" style="">Notes<div class="wprm-decoration-line" style="border-color: #e0e0e0;"></div></h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><ul>
<li>Prep time does not include steps that are already accounted for in the ingredient list, e.g. sliced beef, cut vegetables, etc.</li>
<li>Because lean beef can become tough when pressure cooked, I prefer to use beef chuck or chuck roast. I like to trim off as much of the fat as possible. That way the noodles aren&rsquo;t too greasy.</li>
<li>Try and slice the beef very thinly.&nbsp; That allows it to cook up tender in the time it takes to cook the noodles. <em>If it isn&rsquo;t cut thin, you can end up with tough meat.</em></li>
<li>* If there&rsquo;s still liquid left, you can use the <em><strong>Saute</strong></em> function to allow the liquid to evaporate.</li>
</ul></div></div>
