	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-9275">
	<article id="article-comment-9275">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">razzy 7</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">November 30, 2019 at 8:23 am</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Depending upon the beef used &#8211; I&#8217;ll try flat iron steak, I think 8 minutes would overcook the beef. Thus I&#8217;ll saute it until it&#8217;s just about fully cooked, remove it and add it back when the broccoli is stirred in &#8211; essentially just to warm it with the rest of the ingredients.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-9275" data-commentid="9275" data-postid="9841" data-belowelement="article-comment-9275" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to razzy 7" aria-label="Reply to razzy 7">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-neena bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-9294">
	<article id="article-comment-9294">

		
